BNY Mellon Global Markets CEO Mahoney to Leave Bank in June

-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 
2011-05-03T22:04:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/bny-mellon-global-markets-ceo-mahoney-to-leave-bank-in-june.html
     May 3 (Bloomberg) ---  Bank of New York Mellon Corp. (BK) , the
worldâ€™s largest custody bank, said Richard Mahoney, chief
executive officer of global markets, will retire at the end of
June.  Mahoney, who oversaw foreign exchange, capital markets and
derivatives trading, has been with the New York-based bank for
18 years and had been discussing leaving for more than a year,
according to a statement sent to BNY Mellon employees today.
Mahoney joined the bank in 1993 from Citigroup Inc.  His retirement was earlier today reported by the Wall
